# Caddyfile — TLS reverse proxy for the OpenClaw cockpit
#
# Place this file at /opt/openclaw-control/Caddyfile on the VPS.
# See docs/vps-deployment.md for full setup instructions.
#
# Caddy automatically obtains and renews Let's Encrypt certificates for every
# hostname listed here as long as ports 80/443 are open and DNS resolves to
# this server (72.61.123.4).
#
# Current DNS state (TTL ≈ 50 s):
#   leeheggan.tech  A     72.61.123.4   ← root apex — active
#   www             CNAME leeheggan.tech ← www alias — active
#   cockpit         A     72.61.123.4   ← add this record to enable cockpit subdomain

# Root domain + www — serve the cockpit at the apex while the cockpit subdomain
# A record is pending (or as the permanent home if preferred).
leeheggan.tech, www.leeheggan.tech {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8001
}

# Cockpit subdomain — becomes active once the DNS A record is added.
# Remove this block if you prefer to serve only from the root domain above.
cockpit.leeheggan.tech {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8001
}
